  <p>Great ideas are hard to make happen and wanting to help but not being able to is a frustrating feeling. We know first hand what that feels like. Chae Cramb was a parent trying to open an after school club. Kathryn Kiernan searched for funds for a theater company in her spare time. Keith Martin started a charity event to help raise money for a homeless shelter. Our struggles to find funding revealed a fundamental flaw:  access to funds has and is controlled by a select few.
